HEADWORD: Myriorama
<hw>Myr`i*o*ra"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
numberless + <?/ a sight, fr. <?/ to see.]</ety> <def>A picture made up
of several smaller pictures, drawn upon separate pieces in such a manner
as to admit of combination in many different ways, thus producing a
great variety of scenes or landscapes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

